In c. 17 he says “ non quies, non remissio, non aequalium studia, non ludi, non convivia delectarent ;” where it means such ‘ pursuits as his aequales have) Accordingly this passage should mean ‘that he had such friendship with his elders—such pursuits in common with his aequales,’ that is, he had the same pur-suits as they had, and accordingly was considered to be in the same honourable career.
